                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12964549" author="rcmuir" created="Sun, 28 Nov 2010 13:22:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is actually a bug! Thanks for finding this Shai.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the comparators used in spellcheck are broken: this doesn&apos;t just affect the DirectSpellChecker but also the PlainText and Index-based spellchecks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, if you use the SuggestWordScoreComparator (i think this one is the default), it first sorts based on score, then on document frequency if there is a tie. but if &lt;b&gt;both of these are a tie&lt;/b&gt; the results are undefined... it depends on things such as which order you added documents to your index (for the index-based case)!!!!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch adds a tertiary tie-breaker, which is guaranteed to make the result stable, by using term text (String.compareTo) in these situations.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12964551" author="rcmuir" created="Sun, 28 Nov 2010 13:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding 3.x, as this is a pre-existing bug that affects all spellcheckers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12964627" author="shaie" created="Mon, 29 Nov 2010 04:32:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried the patch and it works. Thanks for fixing it so quickly !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12964702" author="rcmuir" created="Mon, 29 Nov 2010 11:30:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1039979, 1040068 (3x).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks Shai!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
